    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on three core bats primed for big days: **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21), **Mickey Moniak** (75.75), and **Brice Turang** (73.40). **Vinnie Pasquantino** commands the top spot in our rankings, benefiting from a high-efficiency matchup against Davis Martin; the +14% platoon edge and the favorable #3 spot in the order make him an elite start. Meanwhile, **Mickey Moniak** is positioned for a breakout performance against Walker Buehler. His score is bolstered significantly by a +14% platoon advantage and a rare, aggressive matchup against a slow-working pitcher who should allow for opportunistic stolen base attempts. **Brice Turang** remains a locked-in starter, taking advantage of a +19% SP skill edge against Jake Irvin and the premium plate appearances afforded by the leadoff spot.\n\nWhile the top-end production looks stable, several players\u2014including **Gabriel Moreno**, **Dalton Rushing**, and **Corbin Carroll**\u2014are contending with tougher matchups. **Corbin Carroll** (56.65) enters the day with a lower-than-usual score due to the elite 3.40 xERA of Jes\u00fas Luzardo and the inherent risk of facing a southpaw, though his xwOBA remains a stabilizing factor. On the bench, **Alex Freeland** (52.45) was the most difficult exclusion; he projected well against Kumar Rocker, but his limited batting order position (#8) and the volatility of his current role ultimately kept him on the pine. Managers should monitor lineups closely, as **Gabriel Moreno**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Josh Naylor**, **Brice Turang**, **Max Muncy**, **Trevor Story**, **Austin Riley**, **Mickey Moniak**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **James Wood**, and **Corbin Carroll** all remain in \"Lineup Pending\" status. Risk is particularly elevated for **Gabriel Moreno** and **Corbin Carroll** as they face Luzardo, so keep an eye on confirmed batting orders to ensure the -14% SP skill handicap is minimized by advantageous lineup placement.",
